monthly /ˈmʌnθlɪ/

(monthlies) 

1. ADJ A monthly event or publication happens or appears every month. 每月的; 每月一次的 [ADJ n] 

例： Many people are now having trouble making their monthly house payments. 现在许多人都有支付按月房贷的困难。 

例： Kidscape runs monthly workshops for teachers. 基德思加坡为教师举行每月一次的研讨会。 

2. ADV Monthly is also an adverb. 每月地; 每月一次地 [ADV after v] 

例： In some areas the property price can rise monthly. 有些地区，房价能每月都涨。 

3. N-COUNT You can refer to a publication that is published monthly as a monthly . 月刊 

例： ...a satirical monthly. …一份讽刺月刊。 

4. ADJ Monthly quantities or rates relate to a period of one month. 每月的 [ADJ n] 

例： Consumers are charged a monthly fee above their basic cable costs. 消费者每月被收取高于基本有线费的一笔费用。

